# UIRenderSystem

## Purpose
Owns the live UI canvas and translates all enabled UI entities into in-frame draw events each frame.
Each element's rect is resolved in logical-canvas units via recursive parent-chain traversal (the
root element's parent is the logical canvas): from its own anchor-rect, or, when its parent is a
layout container, from the container's layout (stack or grid). Image entities become a
DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent filling their rect — or, when the image declares a nine-slice border, nine
sub-quads (corners at the texture-pixel border size, edges/center stretched, each with its own UV
sub-rect). Text entities become a DrawUIStringInFrameEvent whose glyph block is positioned within the rect per
the text's own alignment. Sizing has two modes: when TextComponent.m_FixedFontSize is 0 (labels) the
font is auto-fit so the whole string fills the rect; when it is positive (body/dialogue text) the font
renders at that exact em height, and if m_WordWrap is set the string is wrapped to the rect width via
Font::WrapString before measuring and emitting (so prose stays a consistent size and stays inside the
box instead of shrinking). The text's m_VisibleChars is forwarded onto the draw event to drive the
typewriter reveal; the layout is always computed on the full string so revealed glyphs never reflow. Each draw event also carries the element's effective clip rect (the intersection of
ancestor UIClip rects) converted to window pixels for the renderer's scissor. The nesting depth is
encoded as the Z component of the transform, providing draw-layer ordering (children render over
parents).

On the first frame it defers creation of both RendererConfigSingletonComponent (the live UI canvas
state) and UICameraSingletonComponent (the renderer's screen-space UI camera), then returns early;
rendering begins from the second frame. Guards on EngineConfigSingletonComponent and
ResourceMapSingletonComponent presence.

## UI Canvas (ADR 0005)
Each frame (once the canvas config exists and the engine config + resources are present) the system
refreshes the live UI canvas before laying out elements:
- Seeds the reference resolution + match factor from EngineConfigSingletonComponent.
- Determines the live window client size — from a WindowResizeEventComponent raised this frame, or
  seeded once from the engine config's window resolution and retained across resize-less frames.
- Derives the UI scale factor with the Unity-style "match width or height" rule (log2 blend between
  the window/reference width and height ratios), and the logical canvas (window size in reference
  units = window / scale) that layout and hit-testing both resolve against.
- Points UICameraSingletonComponent's orthographic projection at the logical canvas (y-down,
  top-left origin), keeping the renderer's UI pass independent of the gameplay camera. The camera's
  vertical bounds account for the renderer's Y-flip (true on DirectX11) so canvas y=0 maps to the top
  of the screen on both flip conventions.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read |
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | read / write |
| WindowResizeEventComponent | read |
| BaseComponent | read |
| ImageComponent | read |
| TextComponent | read |
| LayoutContainerComponent | read |
| UIClipComponent | read |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| RendererConfigSingletonComponent | add (deferred) / write | Created on first frame; refreshed each frame with the live scale factor + logical canvas |
| UICameraSingletonComponent | add (deferred) / write | Renderer-side (pg::) screen-space UI camera; created on first frame, projection synced to the logical canvas each frame |
| DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent | add (inframe) | One per enabled image entity; Z encodes hierarchy depth |
| DrawUIStringInFrameEvent | add (inframe) | One per enabled text entity; Z encodes hierarchy depth |
